                    <span>I work in the bottom 3 OSI layers and pretty much refer back to the same 3 books all the time:<BR>1. Ethernet by Charlie Spurgeon<BR>2. TCP/IP Vol 1 by W.Richard Stevens<BR>3. Switched, Fast and Gig Ethernet by Breyer & Riley<BR>These 3 books are tops. <BR>The Switch Book belongs right up there with these three.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">One of ze best !!</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
